Occurrent Emergency Department Visits for Suspected All Drug and Opioid Overdose

County 1

January 14, 2019


The following report contains a review of information on emergency department (ED) visits for suspected all drug, opioid, heroin, and non-heroin opioid overdoses identified in data reported to the Rapid Health Information NetwOrk (RHINO) for hospitals in County 1. Suspected overdoses are detected in our data by querying the contents of chief complaint and discharge diagnosis using ESSENCE Chief Complaint Discharge Diagnosis (CCDD) categories. Since these are not confirmed by lab results, counts in this report may differ from the true value. The timeframe of data for this report is from 2017-Q1 through 2018-Q3 (the first and last quarters for which data is complete for 75% of EDs in County 1). At the time of creating this report, 100% of hospitals in County 1 were sending data to Washington States syndromic surveillance program.

Note: please do not use the data in this report for public dissemination

Notes on the data:

  • Data was pulled for this report on 14 January, 2019.
  • Records restricted to patients 11 years old.
  • Includes all records from facilities located in the county, regardless of patient location of residence.
  • Suspected overdose visits may include visits in which substance use/abuse is mentioned rather than an acute overdose.
  • Data are preliminary based on information available reported to RHINO and may change. Sensitivity and specificity rely heavily on the completeness and detail provided in emergency department records. As a result, some visits for true overdoses may be missed and others may be misclassified as an overdose.


Syndromes used :

  1. CDC All Drug v1 query
  2. CDC Opioid Overdose v2 query
  3. CDC Heroin Overdose v4 query
  4. Non-Heroin Opioid Overdose: Calculated by subtracting Heroin Overdose v4 CCDD Category counts from Opioid Overdose v2 CCDD Category counts
